Description:
GRISHAM'S BEST ONE YET
"Legal thrillers written by John Grisham are cool, but have you seen 18 Grisham Drive?!"
If not, you must. Because if they gave out Pulitzer Prize's for houses this one would be the 2019 winner, hands down.
Firstly, the house is perfectly positioned. With the enviable 3809 postcode, the property is located within the heart of Arcadia which means you're walking distance from Bridgewood Primary School, Officer Secondary School, public transport and a few really awesome parks.
The house also includes:
- 3 bedrooms, master with en-suite and walk-in robe;
- Large open plan living/dining room;
- Quaint courtyard;
- Heating, cooling and ceiling fans;
- Modern kitchen with walk-in pantry;
- Double car garage;
- Landscaped yards both front and back.
Book in an inspection today. Pun intended.

SPOT ON, DODSON!
"The great start up property."
Whether it's a first home, your first foray into an investment or your first step into a new chapter in life, this property will be there for you. The near-new home is soundly built and carries all the benefits you'd expect to find in a new home.
Best of all, the location is enviable. The property is located within walking distance to Maranatha Christian School and public transport. And with the planned retail complex opening within 2 years this makes this position even more appealing to those with vision to the future.
The house itself features:
- 3 decent size bedrooms, the master with en-suite and walk-in robe;
- Large open plan living/dining room;
- Modern kitchen with stone bench tops and 900mm appliances;
- Heating and cooling;
- Double car garage;
- Awesome backyard - the entire blocks spans over 380sqm.
